    "summary": "Dennis loves researching and teaching the intersections between law, politics, conflict and development.  As an academic, he brings to his work, skills developed over 8 years\u2019 experience in university teaching and research roles and the application of specific research techniques including Qualitative Comparative Analysis and Causal Process Tracing.  He enhances his research output with analytical tools such as VOSViewer and NVivo. He also has expertise in digital assessment processes within higher education.\n\nOutside academia Dennis has 12 years\u2019  experience in development projects management and youth training including Model United Nations programs. He has received international recognition for some of these. In September 2013 he received the Outstanding Young Person Award from the Junior Chambers International in Osaka, Japan and in 2009 he was selected by the United Nations Department of Public Information to lead the organisation of the first ever Global Model United Nations conference in Geneva, Switzerland.  \n\nHe shares his thoughts and reflections through his personal blog: www.developtodevelop.wordpress.com",
